{
  "text": "The basic method, in this approach, was developed by Goldstein et al in 1988 [CITATION_1] . Its principle is to find the most appropriate way to unwrappe the phase by ensuring the coherence of the outcome. It is based on the following properties: \uf0a7 No error propagation over a closed path if and only if the sum of the phase differences corrected along this path is zero.",
  "citation_candidates": [
